## 3. Critical Technical Rules

**⚠️ THESE RULES MUST NEVER BE VIOLATED**

### Rule 1: Use Dependency Injection via GetIt

All services must be accessed through the GetIt service locator. Never instantiate services directly.

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
final authService = locator<AuthService>();
await authService.login(credentials);

// ❌ WRONG
final authService = AuthService(); // Direct instantiation
```

**Why**: Ensures singleton pattern, testability, centralized lifecycle management.

---

### Rule 2: Use Riverpod for State Management

UI state must be managed with Riverpod. Do not use StatefulWidgets for complex state.

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
class MyWidget extends ConsumerWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    final myState = ref.watch(myProvider);
    return Text(myState.message);
  }
}

// ❌ WRONG
class MyWidget extends StatefulWidget {
  // Manual state management
}
```

**Why**: Provides reactive state management, better testability.

---

### Rule 3: Background-First Design

Core monitoring logic belongs in background services (`lib/core/services/`), not the UI layer.

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
// In lib/core/services/data_collector_service.dart
class DataCollectorService {
  Future<void> collectSmsData() async {
    final smsList = await _smsCollector.collect();
    await _storageService.saveSmsData(smsList);
  }
}

// ❌ WRONG
// Complex data collection logic in widget
```

**Why**: Ensures monitoring continues even when UI is closed.

---

### Rule 4: Use Native Bridges for Platform Features

Access platform-specific APIs through established MethodChannel bridges.

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
class SmsCollector {
  static const _channel = MethodChannel('com.xpsafeconnect/sms');

  Future<List<SmsMessage>> collect() async {
    final result = await _channel.invokeMethod('getSmsMessages');
    return result.map((e) => SmsMessage.fromJson(e)).toList();
  }
}

// ❌ WRONG
// Trying to access Android APIs directly from Dart
```

**Why**: Flutter cannot directly access platform APIs. MethodChannels bridge Dart ↔ Native.

---

### Rule 5: Internationalize All User-Facing Text

Use localization files for ALL text displayed in the UI. No hardcoded strings.

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
Text(AppLocalizations.of(context)!.welcomeMessage);

// ❌ WRONG
Text('Welcome'); // Hardcoded
```

**Why**: App must support French (primary) and English.

---

### Rule 6: Handle Errors Gracefully and Securely

Wrap all fallible operations in try-catch blocks. Use Firebase Crashlytics for reporting.

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
try {
  await _apiClient.syncData(data);
} on DioException catch (e, stackTrace) {
  await FirebaseCrashlytics.instance.recordError(e, stackTrace);
  _notificationService.showError(AppLocalizations.of(context)!.syncErrorMessage);
} catch (e, stackTrace) {
  await FirebaseCrashlytics.instance.recordError(e, stackTrace);
}

// ❌ WRONG
await _apiClient.syncData(data); // No error handling
```

**Why**: Network/platform calls can fail. Users should see friendly messages.

